What is Constructor Chaining?

ðŸ‘‰ Calling one constructor from another constructor is called constructor chaining.
In inheritance, this means:

Child class constructor calls Parent class constructor automatically.

class Parent {
    Parent() { }        // Default constructor

    Parent(int a) {
        System.out.println("Parent Constructor");
    }
}

class Child extends Parent {
    Child(int b) {
        System.out.println("Child constructor");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Child obj = new Child(10);
    }
}

